token2-fido-bridge (0.1.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix snap-confined Firefox support: match the virtual UHID device by parent
    kernel name (KERNELS) instead of the nonexistent HID_ID property, so the
    snap_firefox_firefox udev tag is applied correctly.

 -- Token2 <support@token2.com>  Mon, 13 Jul 2026 22:00:00 +0000

token2-fido-bridge (0.1.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial release. Native C++ FIDO2 PC/SC-to-USB-HID bridge.
  * Single static binary (~250 KB) vs multi-MB Python equivalents.
  * Configurable VID/PID (default Token2 349e:0001).
  * systemd service, udev rule, uhid module auto-load; .deb/.rpm packaging.

 -- Token2 <support@token2.com>  Mon, 13 Jul 2026 21:00:00 +0000
